free.jin
Class GameListItem

java.lang.Object
  free.jin.GameListItem
Direct Known Subclasses:
HistoryListItem, LibListItem, SearchListItem, StoredListItem
public abstract class GameListItem
extends java.lang.Object

An encapsulation of the properties that any game list item has. The superclass of all specific game list items. Instances of this class are immutable, and so should instances of its subclasses be.

Creates a new GameListItem with the given properties.

Parameters:
index - The index of the game. The actual meaning may be redefined by the subclass.
gameID - The id of the game - something that uniquely identifies it.
dateString - The date of the game. Whether this is end, start, estimated time of beginning or anything else depends on the subclass.
timeString - The time of the game. Whether this is end, start, estimated time of beginning or anything else depends on the subclass.
whiteName - The name of the player with the white pieces.
blackName - The name of the player with the black pieces.
whiteTime - The initial amount of time on the clock of the player with the white pieces, in milliseconds.
whiteInc - The amount of time added to the clock of the player with the white pieces every time he makes a move, in milliseconds.
blackTime - The initial amount of time on the clock of the player with the black pieces, in milliseconds.
blackInc - The amount of time added to the clock of the player with the black pieces every time he makes a move, in milliseconds.
whiteRating - The rating of the player with the white pieces.
blackRating - The rating of the player with the black pieces.
isRated - True if the game is rated, false otherwise.
variantName - The name of the wild variant of the game.
ratingCategoryString - The name of the category to which the game belongs.
eco - The ECO code of the game.
